.SH NAME
dotty-git-sync - Fetch trunk, clean merged layers, refresh PR maps, rebase+resign if diverged.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty git sync [--continue | --abort] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Synchronise the current stack with trunk:
.IP "  1." 5
Fetch upstream/origin
.IP "  2." 5
Drop layers already on trunk (default: delete local + origin branches)
.IP "  3." 5
If any open layer diverged from trunk — or no longer contains the layer
 below it, because new commits landed mid-stack — prompt to rebase the
 open stack and re-sign each rewritten layer (use --continue / --abort
 around conflicts)
.IP "  4." 5
Force-with-lease push the rewritten branches and return to the branch
 the sync started on
.IP "  5." 5
Refresh the stack visualisation on any open PR whose body is stale,
 preserving descriptions edited on GitHub

.PP
Config: git config dotty.stack.cleanup false  # keep merged branches


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--abort\fP[=false]
	abort an in-progress stack rebase

.PP
\fB--continue\fP[=false]
	resume after resolving rebase conflicts

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for sync

.PP
\fB-y\fP, \fB--yes\fP[=false]
	rebase+resign without prompting when diverged


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty git sync
  dotty git sync --continue
  dotty git sync --yes
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-git(1)\fP
